I'm using [nomnoml](https://github.com/skanaar/nomnoml) to transform a DSL into a diagram which uses canvas:

```js
var canvas = document.getElementById('target-canvas');
var source = '[nomnoml] is -> [awesome]';
nomnoml.draw(canvas, source);
```

I'm passing the UML DSL to the a TextProvider using a query string argument:

```ts
let data = encodeURIComponent(svg);
let url = `${TsUMLProvider.scheme}://authority/${TsUMLProvider.scheme}?uml=${data}`;
let previewUri = vscode.Uri.parse(url);

return vscode.commands.executeCommand(
    "vscode.previewHtml",
    previewUri,
    vscode.ViewColumn.Two
).then((s) => { console.log('done.'); }, vscode.window.showErrorMessage);
```

```ts
// ...
public provideTextDocumentContent(uri: vscode.Uri): string {
        this.uml = uri.query.split("uml=")[1]; // I have the UML DSL!
        return `<!DOCTYPE html>
                    <html>
                        <head></head>
                        <body>
                            <div id="diagram"><!-- RENDER HERE! --></div>
                       </body>
                    </html>`;
}
```

I need to run the following:

```js
let node = document.getElementById('#diagram');
nomnoml.draw(node, this.uml);
```

How can I access the DOM after the `vscode.TextDocumentContentProvider` is rendered on screen by `vscode.previewHtml`? 

Thanks!
